<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-26-0329 </DOCNO><TEXT>A need for small installations which can exploit wastes, particularlyfrom agriculture, is discussed. For a local briquetting press, investmentcosts are not high and markets are readily at hand. A briquetting presssuitable for use in a village must be inexpensive, easy to operate, energyefficient and suited for all types of agricultural wastes. It must notrequire sophisticated storage space for the raw material, finished productsor drying equipment.</TEXT></DOC>